---
import PortfolioLayout from '../layouts/PortfolioLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---
<PortfolioLayout title="Mike Harry - Agentic AI & ML Portfolio">
  <header>
    <div>
      <span class="header_text">
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; gap: 16px;">
          <h1 style="margin: 0;">Mike Harry</h1>
          <button id="resume-btn" class="btn btn-primary" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#resume" style="font-size: 13px; padding: 4px 16px; white-space: nowrap;">
            Show Résumé...
          </button>
        </div>
        <div class="resume_wrapper">
    <div id="resume" class="collapse">
      <div class="resume-content">

        <div class="header">
          <img src="img/mh-headshot.jpg" alt="Michael Harry" class="headshot" />
          <h1>Michael Harry</h1>
          <div class="contact">
            (919) 917-3177 <span>|</span>
            <a href="mailto:michaelharry88@gmail.com">michaelharry88@gmail.com</a> <span>|</span>
            Apex, NC
          </div>
          <div class="contact" style="margin-top: 3pt;">
            <a href="http://mikeharry.info">mikeharry.info</a> <span>|</span>
            <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/michaelharry88/">linkedin.com/in/michaelharry88</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2>Summary</h2>
        <div class="summary">
          <div class="summary-para">Distinguished Architect/Engineer with 20+ years of experience designing and delivering developer platforms, tool ecosystems, and cloud-native infrastructure at enterprise scale.</div>
          <div class="summary-para">I am currently focused on generative AI and agentic systems to accelerate developer productivity and increase quality. I am both a strategic leader, responsible for the generative AI roadmap for Walmart's Enterprise and Cloud Infrastructure team, and a hands-on builder of early-stage, emerging technology solutions, carrying them from proof of concept through production-grade, enterprise systems.</div>
          <div class="summary-para">I combine deep cloud-native infrastructure experience with full-stack development, machine learning foundations, and a track record of building self-service systems that compress delivery by orders of magnitude and transform how engineering teams work.</div>
        </div>

        <h2>Technical Skills</h2>
        <div class="skills-grid">
          <div class="label">GenAI &amp; Agents</div>
          <div class="value">WIBEY (Walmart AI Agentic Platform), Claude, Copilot, MCP Server Development, LLM Integration (MCP and A2A), AI-Augmented Development &amp; Testing</div>

          <div class="label">Languages &amp; Tools</div>
          <div class="value">Python (multi-threaded), FastMCP, FastAPI, Flask, pytest, Shell Scripting, Java/J2EE (multi-threaded), Spring, React, Vite, Tailwind CSS, Vaadin, REST, TypeScript, JavaScript, Node.js, SQL, HTML/CSS, C/C++</div>

          <div class="label">ML &amp; Data Science</div>
          <div class="value">PyTorch, MLFlow, Optuna, scikit-learn, pandas, NumPy, Jupyter Notebooks, R</div>

          <div class="label">Cloud &amp; Infra</div>
          <div class="value">GCP Services (Compute, Cloud Functions, BigQuery, IAM, Dataproc, GCS, Log Sinks), Azure, OpenStack, WCNP (Kubernetes), Docker, Rancher, Swarm</div>

          <div class="label">Enterprise Platforms</div>
          <div class="value">KITT CI/CD (Argo CD / GitHub Actions), Concord (Argo Workflows), OneOps (Terraform/Ansible), PingFederate (OAuth 2.0), Akeyless (HashiCorp Vault), SonarQube, Snyk, GitHub, Looper (Jenkins), DPaaS (Dataproc), AFaaS (Airflow), Prometheus, Grafana, OpenTelemetry, PostgreSQL, BigQuery, MySQL, Kafka, JMS</div>
        </div>

        <h2>Professional Experience</h2>

        <div class="job">
          <div class="job-header">
            <span class="job-company">Walmart Global Technology</span>
            <span class="job-location">Sunnyvale, CA (Remote)</span>
          </div>
          <div class="job-role">
            <span class="job-title">Distinguished Architect/Engineer</span>
            <span class="job-dates">January 2025 – Present</span>
          </div>
          <ul>
            <li>Own roadmap and technical strategy for developer productivity, tools, and processes for WIBEY, Walmart's agentic orchestration platform for developers</li>
            <li>Architect and hands-on lead for PoC-to-production delivery of MCP Servers, shared WIBEY workflow Skills, and generative AI management dashboards</li>
            <li>Design and build autonomous, self-healing end-to-end SDLC agent workflows that drive measurable gains in delivery velocity and code quality</li>
            <li>Mentor senior engineers and drive team-wide adoption of AI-augmented development practices across the organization</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="job-role">
            <span class="job-title">Principal Cloud &amp; Data Architect/Engineer</span>
            <span class="job-dates">February 2022 – January 2025</span>
          </div>
          <ul>
            <li>Led architecture for Walmart's multicloud capacity management and optimization platform across OpenStack, GCP, and Azure — unifying compute, storage, and network visibility across private and public cloud estates</li>
            <li>Designed ML forecasting models to predict client demand and infrastructure needs, enabling proactive capacity planning and rightsizing across regions and cloud providers</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="job-role">
            <span class="job-title">Cloud / Big Data Platform Architect</span>
            <span class="job-dates">September 2016 – January 2022</span>
          </div>
          <ul>
            <li>Led team of 20 globally dispersed architects, engineers, and contractors through transformation from system administration to a DevOps model emphasizing automation and self-service</li>
            <li>Architect and lead engineer for migration of Walmart's on-prem big data platforms to public cloud; designed the Team Spaces, DPaaS and AFaaS infrastructure provisioning system enabling self-service ephemeral clusters, reducing delivery time from days to minutes</li>
            <li>Implemented Infrastructure as Code (IaC) practices with automated maintenance, upgrades, and CI/CD pipelines using Python, Airflow, Jenkins, Git and JSON</li>
            <li>Developed cloud-native architectures enabling eCommerce teams to deploy mission-critical applications to private cloud platforms with full CI/CD, regression testing, and security inspection</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="job">
          <div class="job-header">
            <span class="job-company">Cisco Systems</span>
            <span class="job-location">Research Triangle Park, NC</span>
          </div>
          <div class="job-role">
            <span class="job-title">Cloud &amp; Compute Domain Architect</span>
            <span class="job-dates">May 2010 – September 2016</span>
          </div>
          <ul>
            <li>Owned the architecture blueprint and technology roadmap for Cisco IT's global data center compute, storage, and virtualization infrastructure, standardized across OpenStack, VMware, Docker, and Cisco UCS</li>
            <li>Designed and delivered Containers as a Service (CaaS) platform supporting multi-tenant microservices using Docker, Kubernetes, and OpenShift, built iteratively using Agile sprints</li>
            <li>Consolidated disparate IaaS and PaaS provisioning into a unified self-service portal for compute, storage, network and application services, reducing provisioning times from weeks to minutes</li>
            <li>Converged compute resources into a general-purpose shared pool, eliminating application-specific infrastructure silos and achieving a 300% increase in resource efficiency</li>
            <li>Solution Architect for Metro Virtual Data Center (MVDC), a dual-datacenter resiliency system enabling failover for loss of an entire facility within a single metro region</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="job-role">
            <span class="job-title">Developer Productivity Architect</span>
            <span class="job-dates">January 2006 – May 2010</span>
          </div>
          <ul>
            <li>Led the creation of the inaugural Cisco IT Development Frameworks and Tools (DFT) team to standardize enterprise-wide SDLC: tool selection, frameworks, testing (unit, functional and security), packaging, deployment, source control, and runtime monitoring</li>
            <li>Managed a team of architects, PMs, and engineers delivering SDLC tooling and establishing standards across all Cisco IT engineering departments</li>
            <li>Implemented Eclipse IDE plugins to automate setup and scaffolding of standardized frameworks, tools and processes</li>
            <li>Introduced Agile development practices across a 22-person, globally distributed team</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="job-role">
            <span class="job-title">Senior Architect</span>
            <span class="job-dates">February 2001 – January 2006</span>
          </div>
          <ul>
            <li>Architected and led engineering of an integrated suite of web-based developer tools including bug tracking, project management, workflow management, and an information portal, used enterprise-wide by Cisco engineering teams</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="job">
          <div class="job-header">
            <span class="job-company">BuildNet</span>
            <span class="job-location">Research Triangle Park, NC</span>
          </div>
          <div class="job-role">
            <span class="job-title">Chief Architect / Director of IT Applications</span>
            <span class="job-dates">March 1997 – February 2001</span>
          </div>
          <ul>
            <li>Owned the overall architecture and design of the BuildNet system, including subsystems for e-business, online catalog, member information, access control, and product data management</li>
            <li>Responsible for the successful deployment of 8 new corporate information systems including enterprise-wide sales, support, marketing, billing, financial, budgeting, HR and payroll systems</li>
            <li>Starting with 1 member, grew team to over 25 people, establishing an exceptional team for customizing, deploying, and supporting the BuildNet Enterprise IT Applications</li>
            <li>Responsible for staffing, budget planning and administration, strategic planning, and inter-department coordination for all aspects of enterprise information systems</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <h2>Additional Experience</h2>
        <div class="additional-exp">
          <div class="add-role">
            <div><span class="add-company">Questra Consulting</span>, <span class="add-title">Software Engineer</span></div>
            <span class="add-dates">1995 – 1997</span>
          </div>
          <div class="add-role">
            <div><span class="add-company">Northeast Parallel Architectures Center (Syracuse University)</span>, <span class="add-title">Research Assistant</span></div>
            <span class="add-dates">1993 – 1995</span>
          </div>
          <div class="add-role">
            <div><span class="add-company">U.S. Naval Academy</span>, <span class="add-title">Systems Programmer</span></div>
            <span class="add-dates">1992 – 1993</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2>Education</h2>
        <div class="edu-item">
          <span class="degree">Postgraduate Coursework</span>
          <div class="edu-row edu-detail">
            <span><strong>Computer Science / Data Science</strong> · North Carolina State University</span>
            <span class="school">2005 – 2025</span>
          </div>
          <div class="edu-detail">Neural Networks (2025) · Automated Learning &amp; Data Analysis (2023)</div>
        </div>
        <div class="edu-item">
          <div class="edu-row">
            <div><span class="degree">M.S. Computer Science</span> · Syracuse University</div>
            <div class="school">1995</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="edu-item">
          <div class="edu-row">
            <div><span class="degree">B.S. Computer Science</span> · Rochester Institute of Technology</div>
            <div class="school">1993</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2>Certifications</h2>
        <ul class="certs">
          <li>IBM Computer Vision &amp; Deep Learning Specialization (6-Course Certificate)</li>
          <li>Johns Hopkins Data Science Specialization (10-Course Certificate)</li>
          <li>Certified Scrum Master (Scrum.org PSM I)</li>
        </ul>

      <div style="display: flex; justify-content: center; padding: 16px 0 8px;">
        <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#resume" style="font-size: 13px;">
          Hide Résumé ↑
        </button>
      </div>
      </div>
    </div>
        </div>
        <h3 class="header_chiclet">
          Agentic AI, Machine Learning and Computer Vision Project Portfolio
        </h3>
      </span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="portfolioPage">
    <div class="portfolioCards">

      <!-- Project1: WARP -->
